&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;Who is Credible?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Credible is a leading U.S. consumer finance marketplace, transforming the way consumers access and compare financial products. We operate at a consumer and enterprise level. On the consumer side, we help millions of people make smarter financial decisions by comparing personalized, pre-qualified offers across student loans, personal loans, mortgages, credit cards, and insurance — all without impacting their credit score. On the enterprise side, we power financial product comparison and distribution through deep integrations and partnerships with lenders, insurance carriers, and financial institutions, as well as providing marketplace technology and capabilities to third-party partners and distribution channels.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are hiring a Growth Lead to be the team-lead anchor of Credible&#39;s Israel-based paid marketing operation. The role starts with deep Google Ads / SEM ownership, managing large-scale campaigns across Credible&#39;s core financial verticals and rapidly expands into paid social, remarketing, display, and emerging channels as the team scales through FY27.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will own a vertical end-to-end, mentor analysts, and help build the operational playbook that turns the team into a world-class performance engine. This is the right role if you&#39;ve been the go-to person on a high-spend account, you know when to optimize and when to rebuild, and you&#39;re ready to lead a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own a group of verticals end-to-end: manage campaign structure, bid strategy, keyword expansion, ad copy, and channel mix for your assigned vertical(s) across Google Ads, Bing, and over time paid social and remarketing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the Israel team: onboard new analysts, run weekly syncs, review account changes, and define best-practice standards — you&#39;re the technical and strategic anchor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive conversion signal quality: work with the BI team to automate offline conversion uploads and lead the shift to value-based bidding across verticals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shape channel strategy: define the expansion roadmap beyond search into paid social, remarketing (Google Display, RLSA, Meta custom audiences), and own the go/no-go decisions with the Head of Performance Marketing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cross-functional collaboration: work closely with Product on landing page performance, CRO experiments, and conversion funnel improvements; partner with Content and SEO on messaging alignment, keyword strategy, and creative direction across channels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Systematic testing cadence: run structured A/B tests on copy, audiences, landing pages, and bid strategies; document learnings so the full team benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performance reporting: build and own weekly vertical scorecards; flag anomalies, escalate risks, and present a clear narrative on what&#39;s working and why&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SEM &amp;amp; channel knowledge base: document strategies, account structures, and channel playbooks so institutional knowledge compounds&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EDUCATION &amp;amp; EXPERIENCE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience: 5+ years of hands-on paid media management with a primary focus on Google Ads / SEM performance marketing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Spend scale: proven experience managing $1M+/month in Google Ads; demonstrated GPM or ROAS improvement over time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Channel breadth: meaningful experience beyond pure search — paid social (Meta), remarketing, display, or PMAX — or a clear track record of expanding into new channels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team leadership: 1–3 years mentoring or managing junio

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;Who is Credible?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Credible is a leading U.S. consumer finance marketplace, transforming the way consumers access and compare financial products. We operate at a consumer and enterprise level. On the consumer side, we help millions of people make smarter financial decisions by comparing personalized, pre-qualified offers across student loans, personal loans, mortgages, credit cards, and insurance — all without impacting their credit score. On the enterprise side, we power financial product comparison and distribution through deep integrations and partnerships with lenders, insurance carriers, and financial institutions, as well as providing marketplace technology and capabilities to third-party partners and distribution channels.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are hiring Performance Marketing Analysts (also titled Growth Specialists) for Credible&#39;s Israel-based paid marketing team. These are mid-senior individual-contributor roles that start in SEM — owning Google Ads campaigns hands-on across Credible&#39;s financial verticals — and grow into multi-channel performance roles covering remarketing, paid social, and emerging formats as the team expands through FY27.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will report to the Senior Performance Marketing Lead and work closely with the Head of Performance Marketing in San Francisco. This is a high-autonomy role with real budget ownership, clear targets, and a fast path to broader channel responsibility.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Campaign ownership: build, manage, and optimize SEM campaigns across assigned verticals — keyword research, ad copy, bid management, negative keyword hygiene, and match type strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Channel expansion: after 2–3 months, expand ownership into remarketing (RLSA, Display, Custom Audiences) and contribute to social campaign management alongside the team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performance analysis: monitor daily performance against GPM and revenue targets; identify underperforming campaigns and take corrective action proactively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keyword &amp;amp; niche expansion: identify high-intent keyword clusters not yet in the account and build structured campaigns to capture incremental volume&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ad copy &amp;amp; creative testing: run A/B tests on headlines, descriptions, and call-to-action variants; document results and apply learnings across campaigns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Landing page alignment: ensure campaign relevance and Quality Score by coordinating with the PM/CRO team on landing page content and URL structure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reporting: contribute to weekly performance reports; flag issues with clear context and recommended actions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tool fluency: use Google Ads scripts, bulk uploads, and Editor to execute changes efficiently at scale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EDUCATION &amp;amp; EXPERIENCE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience: 3 years of hands-on paid media management, primarily Google Ads, in a performance/direct-response environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Spend scale: experience managing $500K/month in Google Ads; demonstrated ROAS improvement or CPA reduction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Channel awareness: some exposure to paid social (Meta/Facebook), remarketing, or display — even if not your primary channel — and enthusiasm to expand&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical skills: solid understanding of Smart Bidding, keyword match types, Quality Score levers, search term analysis, and campaign structure best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data comfort: able to pull reports in Google Ads and Google Sheets, build basic pivot tables, and identify meaningful trends&lt;/li&gt;
